## Update the ~/.ssh/config profile with the below commands to make the ssh login simpler. E.g., ssh gauravsinghal@<ip address> to ssh gs 
Host gs
    HostName <ip address>
    User <ssh username> ##e.g., gauravsinghal
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/gs-aws-key.pem ## if .pem key is generated on the AWS, else deactivate the command
    IdentitiesOnly yes


